b'@SheepOfWallStrt @chamath @chamat In 2016 I was working at a Family Office. I bought $TECK at $3. A mining guy asked why I was buying it. It could go bankrupt. \n\nDid I hear this story before? Sold at $25.'

b'@chamath @chamat My good Canada story can\'t finish with $TECK. On March 6, 2009, I got a hold of a report by ML - "Debt is Death", listing companies that may go bankrupt. $TECK was on the list - Copper, Zinc and Met Coal, a prominent Canadian family owning a large stake. I bought at $2.70.'
